77
00:08:13.587 --> 00:08:16.291
♪ ♪

78
00:08:27.337 --> 00:08:30.272
♪ ♪

79
00:08:42.715 --> 00:08:45.419
♪ ♪

80
00:09:13.647 --> 00:09:17.947
Okay. I guess we'll just
follow that terrifying noise.

81
00:09:25.989 --> 00:09:26.824
Come on.

82
00:09:26.825 --> 00:09:28.793
You're not
the scared guy anymore.

83
00:09:29.663 --> 00:09:32.598
Yes. I am! People don't change!

84
00:09:49.815 --> 00:09:52.948
There's the problem.

85
00:09:58.890 --> 00:10:00.626
Ooh.

86
00:10:06.106 --> 00:10:07.832
Put the bricks back.
Put the bricks back.

87
00:10:07.833 --> 00:10:11.275
I looked down that hole.
and the devil looked back.

88
00:10:28.854 --> 00:10:31.922
Hey. It's all right.

89
00:10:37.060 --> 00:10:39.764
♪ ♪

90
00:10:40.635 --> 00:10:42.965
Easy.

91
00:10:49.072 --> 00:10:51.282
- Ah.
- Hey. okay.

92
00:10:51.283 --> 00:10:52.778
Okay. now.

93
00:10:52.779 --> 00:10:54.681
What's your name. little guy?

94
00:10:54.682 --> 00:10:55.946
Yoshi.

95
00:10:55.947 --> 00:10:57.387
Nice to meet you. Yoshi.

96
00:10:57.388 --> 00:10:59.884
How did you get in a warp pipe?

97
00:10:59.885 --> 00:11:00.852
Oh...

98
00:11:03.086 --> 00:11:05.790
♪ ♪

99
00:11:12.634 --> 00:11:15.338
♪ ♪

100
00:11:21.973 --> 00:11:24.777
("Hypnotize"
by The Notorious B.I.G. plays)

101
00:11:24.778 --> 00:11:27.449
Out of the road!

102
00:11:39.661 --> 00:11:42.860
We got a 1-9-8-1 monkey...

103
00:11:47.834 --> 00:11:50.901
Mm? Wh...? Oh!

104
00:12:01.815 --> 00:12:03.354
("Pipe Travel" plays)

105
00:12:05.258 --> 00:12:07.490
I guess we'll never know.

106
00:12:12.155 --> 00:12:13.496
♪ ♪

107
00:12:13.497 --> 00:12:15.531
- Found the problem.
- Ah.

108
00:12:22.770 --> 00:12:24.903
- Hola. Yoshi.
- Yoshi.

109
00:12:24.904 --> 00:12:26.641
Yoshi. Yoshi.

110
00:12:26.642 --> 00:12:29.380
Yoshi. Yoshi.

111
00:12:29.381 --> 00:12:31.679
All that trouble over a Yoshi.

112
00:12:31.680 --> 00:12:36.177
Yeah. You know. we found
the little fella and...

113
00:12:36.685 --> 00:12:39.213
Where'd he go?

114
00:12:39.622 --> 00:12:40.853
Huh.

115
00:12:40.854 --> 00:12:42.888
Well. he seemed like
a nice guy.

116
00:12:44.088 --> 00:12:46.463
♪ ♪

117
00:12:46.464 --> 00:12:48.762
Rrr. rrr.

118
00:12:48.763 --> 00:12:51.897
He knows that's my bike. right?

119
00:12:51.898 --> 00:12:53.866
♪ ♪

120
00:13:10.950 --> 00:13:13.654
♪ ♪

121
00:13:26.801 --> 00:13:29.439
♪ ♪

122
00:13:32.774 --> 00:13:35.479
Where are you taking us?

123
00:13:35.480 --> 00:13:37.514
Try and enjoy it. Princess.

124
00:13:37.515 --> 00:13:43.013
It's the last place
you'll ever see alive.

125
00:13:47.426 --> 00:13:50.119
♪ ♪

126
00:14:17.984 --> 00:14:20.655
♪ ♪

127
00:14:37.674 --> 00:14:39.268
It's pretty cool. right?

128
00:14:39.269 --> 00:14:42.479
I really think my dad's
gonna love it.

129
00:14:45.682 --> 00:14:47.815
Mama. I'm scared.

130
00:14:47.816 --> 00:14:50.278
It's gonna be all right.

131
00:15:03.766 --> 00:15:05.063
My Koopas.

132
00:15:05.064 --> 00:15:07.296
guess who stole a princess.

133
00:15:07.297 --> 00:15:08.935
Ah...

134
00:15:08.936 --> 00:15:10.838
And not just any princess.

135
00:15:10.839 --> 00:15:15.040
The guardian of the cosmos.
the mother of the stars.

136
00:15:15.041 --> 00:15:19.418
With her powers.
we will destroy the universe!

137
00:15:19.419 --> 00:15:23.147
She will give her life
for our glory!

138
00:15:24.017 --> 00:15:26.084
How's that for a speech?

139
00:15:26.085 --> 00:15:28.954
Very descriptive.

140
00:15:31.992 --> 00:15:33.762
Ow! Ow!

141
00:15:34.566 --> 00:15:38.700
No one hurts my kids.

142
00:15:43.135 --> 00:15:44.971
Go!

143
00:16:04.090 --> 00:16:07.796
The great battle
of my life draws near.

144
00:16:07.797 --> 00:16:12.294
It is time to free my father.

145
00:16:17.433 --> 00:16:20.071
♪ ♪

146
00:16:35.385 --> 00:16:36.495
Think she'll like it?

147
00:16:36.496 --> 00:16:40.961
Mario. do you have feelings
for the princess?

148
00:16:40.962 --> 00:16:42.193
What?!

149
00:16:42.194 --> 00:16:44.129
Oh. what? Can't a guy give
his good buddy

150
00:16:44.130 --> 00:16:48.606
a perfect present to-to show her just
how much she means to him?

151
00:16:48.607 --> 00:16:52.907
♪ When the moon hits your eye ♪

152
00:16:52.908 --> 00:16:54.711
♪ Like a big pizza pie ♪

153
00:16:54.712 --> 00:16:57.813
- ♪ That's... ♪
- ♪ A-Yoshi. ♪

154
00:16:57.814 --> 00:17:00.112
I'm not in love with Peach.

155
00:17:00.113 --> 00:17:02.015
Mwah. mwah.

156
00:17:02.016 --> 00:17:04.886
Let's just go.

157
00:17:04.887 --> 00:17:06.481
♪ ♪

158
00:17:06.482 --> 00:17:09.726
("Too Hot to Stop - Pt. 1"
by The Bar-Kays playing)

159
00:17:09.727 --> 00:17:11.563
♪ ♪

160
00:17:11.564 --> 00:17:12.696
♪ Yeah. yeah ♪

161
00:17:12.697 --> 00:17:16.029
- ♪ Hey. hey ♪
- Say "mushroom."

162
00:17:16.030 --> 00:17:18.801
♪ Yeah... ♪

163
00:17:18.802 --> 00:17:20.769
Ooh.

164
00:17:25.303 --> 00:17:26.842
(gulps) Mmm.

165
00:17:26.843 --> 00:17:28.305
Hey. guys.

166
00:17:28.306 --> 00:17:29.207
Hey. Toad.

167
00:17:29.208 --> 00:17:31.879
Looking good.

168
00:17:32.442 --> 00:17:34.586
Um. who is this?

169
00:17:34.587 --> 00:17:36.852
Yoshi.

170
00:17:36.853 --> 00:17:40.284
- Who could resist that face?
- Aw...

171
00:17:41.990 --> 00:17:43.320
Come on.

172
00:17:43.321 --> 00:17:45.630
So some cool dinosaur
just shows up

173
00:17:45.631 --> 00:17:47.522
and he's now part of the group.

174
00:17:47.523 --> 00:17:50.733
♪ ♪

175
00:17:54.640 --> 00:17:57.136
Hey. uh. have you seen
the princess?

176
00:17:57.137 --> 00:17:58.874
Nope.

177
00:17:58.875 --> 00:18:01.612
♪ ♪

178
00:18:11.591 --> 00:18:14.955
♪ ♪

179
00:18:17.861 --> 00:18:20.554
♪ ♪

180
00:18:30.841 --> 00:18:31.841
Hey.

181
00:18:31.842 --> 00:18:34.041
You're missing your own party.

182
00:18:35.538 --> 00:18:37.979
I hate birthdays.

183
00:18:37.980 --> 00:18:38.782
Yeah.

184
00:18:38.783 --> 00:18:41.477
Luigi spent
his tenth birthday crying.

185
00:18:41.478 --> 00:18:44.656
Said his childhood was over.

186
00:18:45.416 --> 00:18:49.859
Well. the crazy thing is.
today's not my real birthday.

187
00:18:49.860 --> 00:18:52.730
It's just the day
the Toads found me.

188
00:18:52.731 --> 00:18:55.425
They have no idea
where I came from.

189
00:18:55.426 --> 00:19:00.870
I've lived my entire life
wondering where my family is.

190
00:19:00.871 --> 00:19:03.334
That must be so hard.

191
00:19:03.335 --> 00:19:07.810
Sometimes I just feel so lost.

192
00:19:09.407 --> 00:19:12.750
Guess since it's not
your actual birthday.

193
00:19:12.751 --> 00:19:14.653
you don't want a present.

194
00:19:14.654 --> 00:19:15.819
Mario!

195
00:19:15.820 --> 00:19:18.953
All right. Fine. fine.

196
00:19:21.859 --> 00:19:23.859
Oh.

197
00:19:28.096 --> 00:19:29.931
I love it.

198
00:19:34.839 --> 00:19:37.004
Huh?

199
00:19:39.877 --> 00:19:42.273
Whoa.

200
00:19:42.979 --> 00:19:45.716
♪ ♪

201
00:19:55.255 --> 00:19:56.892
Look.

202
00:20:11.370 --> 00:20:13.843
- Wow.
- Whoa.

203
00:20:13.944 --> 00:20:16.406
Whoa.

204
00:20:20.951 --> 00:20:23.083
Oh.

205
00:20:37.561 --> 00:20:40.331
♪ ♪

206
00:20:58.890 --> 00:21:01.616
♪ ♪

207
00:21:28.150 --> 00:21:32.791
Princess Peach.
I finally found you.

208
00:21:32.792 --> 00:21:33.891
Oh.

209
00:21:42.263 --> 00:21:44.626
Feel better now?

210
00:21:45.937 --> 00:21:48.037
I can't believe
it's really you.

211
00:21:48.038 --> 00:21:52.470
Our mama read us so many
bedtime stories about you.

212
00:21:52.471 --> 00:21:54.043
Me?

213
00:21:54.044 --> 00:21:54.978
Are you sure?

214
00:21:54.979 --> 00:21:57.607
She said if anything
ever happened to her.

215
00:21:57.608 --> 00:22:00.984
to find you
and you would help us.

216
00:22:00.985 --> 00:22:04.020
Princess.
our mama's been taken.

217
00:22:04.021 --> 00:22:04.856
What happened?

218
00:22:04.857 --> 00:22:07.749
A giant robot took her
to a scary planet

219
00:22:07.750 --> 00:22:10.455
out beyond the Gateway Galaxy.

220
00:22:10.456 --> 00:22:12.390
Can you help us?

221
00:22:16.000 --> 00:22:18.793
Uh. Peach. sorry. I tried...

222
00:22:18.794 --> 00:22:20.201
Yes. yes.
we were eavesdropping.

223
00:22:20.202 --> 00:22:21.906
Don't you even
think about leaving.

224
00:22:21.907 --> 00:22:24.700
Guys. can we just give
the princess a minute?

225
00:22:24.701 --> 00:22:26.801
She'll figure out what to do.

226
00:22:26.802 --> 00:22:28.473
I disagree. Mario.

227
00:22:28.474 --> 00:22:30.739
Even though my pajamas
say otherwise.

228
00:22:30.740 --> 00:22:32.807
There is nothing to figure out.

229
00:22:32.808 --> 00:22:34.182
She is not leaving.

230
00:22:34.183 --> 00:22:35.414
Yes. yes. yes.

231
00:22:35.415 --> 00:22:36.811
All right. guys. let's go.

232
00:22:36.812 --> 00:22:40.055
We can discuss more
in the morning.

233
00:22:41.454 --> 00:22:43.817
Good night. Princess.

234
00:22:44.094 --> 00:22:46.820
♪ ♪

235
00:22:52.971 --> 00:22:55.302
Toad. pack our things.

236
00:22:55.303 --> 00:22:57.875
♪ ♪

237
00:23:27.104 --> 00:23:28.907
Whoa!

238
00:23:28.908 --> 00:23:31.601
♪ ♪

239
00:23:33.836 --> 00:23:38.014
Woo-hoo-hoo-hoo!

240
00:23:43.153 --> 00:23:44.153
What happened?

241
00:23:44.154 --> 00:23:46.187
She left this for you.

242
00:23:48.521 --> 00:23:49.785
<i>Dear Mustache.</i>

243
00:23:49.786 --> 00:23:52.557
<i>I've gone to the Gateway Galaxy
to begin my search</i>

244
00:23:52.558 --> 00:23:53.822
<i>for the Luma's mom.</i>

245
00:23:53.823 --> 00:23:56.968
<i>I'm leaving the Kingdom
in your hands.</i>

246
00:23:56.969 --> 00:24:00.432
<i>Sincerely. Peach.</i>

247
00:24:01.303 --> 00:24:02.138
"Sincerely."

248
00:24:02.139 --> 00:24:05.174
Ooh la la. That's a good sign.

249
00:24:05.175 --> 00:24:07.044
Princess Peach is gone?

250
00:24:07.045 --> 00:24:08.276
Oh. no!

251
00:24:12.545 --> 00:24:15.282
Everyone. calm down.

252
00:24:15.680 --> 00:24:17.417
The Super Mario Brothers

253
00:24:17.418 --> 00:24:19.881
can take care of the Kingdom.

254
00:24:19.882 --> 00:24:22.619
♪ ♪

255
00:24:49.989 --> 00:24:52.286
("Power-Up" plays)

256
00:25:11.769 --> 00:25:13.803
- Ha!
- ("Power-Up" plays)

257
00:25:27.389 --> 00:25:28.092
Woo-hoo!

258
00:25:28.093 --> 00:25:31.193
♪ ♪

259
00:25:46.111 --> 00:25:48.375
("Pipe Travel" plays)

260
00:26:03.821 --> 00:26:05.558
Now what?

261
00:26:30.782 --> 00:26:33.552
♪ ♪

262
00:26:39.164 --> 00:26:41.363
Hey. big guy.

263
00:26:41.364 --> 00:26:42.199
Aah! Oh.

264
00:26:42.200 --> 00:26:44.168
You scared me.

265
00:26:44.169 --> 00:26:45.400
You wanted to see us?

266
00:26:45.401 --> 00:26:48.029
Don't move. I'll be right up.

267
00:26:50.340 --> 00:26:52.473
♪ Sippin' the soup ♪

268
00:26:52.474 --> 00:26:54.376
♪ Cleaning the paint ♪

269
00:26:56.676 --> 00:27:00.250
♪ And also trim
the bonsai bush. ♪

270
00:27:00.251 --> 00:27:02.548
Here we go.

271
00:27:06.752 --> 00:27:09.819
Hey. Luigi!

272
00:27:10.228 --> 00:27:12.130
What's up. Mario?

273
00:27:13.330 --> 00:27:14.088
Behold.

274
00:27:14.089 --> 00:27:17.795
I made a masterpiece
for Princess Peach.

275
00:27:17.796 --> 00:27:20.061
What do you think?

276
00:27:20.062 --> 00:27:22.172
And be honest.

277
00:27:23.098 --> 00:27:24.901
Love the colors.

278
00:27:24.902 --> 00:27:28.575
The criticism I'd give you
is it's trash.

279
00:27:28.576 --> 00:27:31.941
How dare you look at
my masterpiece and say that!

280
00:27:31.942 --> 00:27:33.712
You think painting is easy?

281
00:27:33.713 --> 00:27:37.649
I'll burn the skin
off your bones!

282
00:27:38.047 --> 00:27:40.224
Wow.

283
00:27:40.225 --> 00:27:41.192
Sorry about that.

284
00:27:41.193 --> 00:27:42.457
That's the old Bowser talking.

285
00:27:42.458 --> 00:27:46.989
Still working through my demons.
I suppose.

286
00:27:46.990 --> 00:27:49.090
All good.

287
00:27:49.091 --> 00:27:50.300
All better now.

288
00:27:50.301 --> 00:27:53.270
Anyway.
it's not just a present.

289
00:27:53.271 --> 00:27:55.096
It's a peace offering.

290
00:27:55.097 --> 00:27:56.372
I'd like her to release me.

291
00:27:56.373 --> 00:28:00.343
Not for good behavior.
for awesome behavior!

292
00:28:00.344 --> 00:28:01.476
She'd never release you.

293
00:28:01.477 --> 00:28:03.973
And don't even ask
about making you big again.

294
00:28:03.974 --> 00:28:06.745
Even though
I'm totally rehabilitated?

295
00:28:06.746 --> 00:28:08.186
Mario. he's really changed.

296
00:28:08.187 --> 00:28:11.222
We're doing a weekly
book club together.

297
00:28:11.223 --> 00:28:12.289
I bring the soup.

298
00:28:12.290 --> 00:28:16.721
She doesn't trust you.
and neither do I.

299
00:28:16.954 --> 00:28:18.658
Oh. you better start
trusting me

300
00:28:18.659 --> 00:28:22.562
or I will eat your soul and...

301
00:28:24.027 --> 00:28:25.896
I'm sorry. that... It's just...

302
00:28:25.897 --> 00:28:27.161
Oh. wow.

303
00:28:27.162 --> 00:28:31.033
All right. You know what. guys.
I'm gonna hit the sack.

304
00:28:31.034 --> 00:28:32.133
I need my eight hours

305
00:28:32.134 --> 00:28:35.444
or else I really turn into a monster.

306
00:28:35.445 --> 00:28:36.973
Ow!

307
00:28:36.974 --> 00:28:38.106
Ow. ow. ow. ow. ow!

308
00:28:39.812 --> 00:28:43.144
Stubbed it! Stubbed it!
Stubbed the dang toe!

309
00:28:45.554 --> 00:28:48.116
Nighty night.

310
00:28:49.657 --> 00:28:51.229
Uh...

311
00:28:59.095 --> 00:29:01.370
Huh?

312
00:29:17.718 --> 00:29:20.488
♪ ♪

313
00:29:43.579 --> 00:29:45.547
We got to get everyone
out of here.

314
00:29:45.548 --> 00:29:48.011
Go. go. go!

315
00:30:16.546 --> 00:30:19.272
♪ ♪

316
00:30:29.658 --> 00:30:32.692
That's everyone. Let's go.

317
00:30:42.440 --> 00:30:44.539
Whoa.

318
00:30:45.938 --> 00:30:48.675
♪ ♪

319
00:30:53.110 --> 00:30:56.782
<i>Mamma mia.</i>

320
00:30:57.620 --> 00:30:59.950
Whoa.

321
00:31:21.941 --> 00:31:23.744
In the name of the Koopas.

322
00:31:23.745 --> 00:31:27.516
I demand that you release
my father.

323
00:31:29.014 --> 00:31:31.521
Over my dead body.

324
00:31:31.522 --> 00:31:34.083
Fine with me.

325
00:31:46.295 --> 00:31:49.671
Why don't we start over
and introduce ourselves?

326
00:31:49.672 --> 00:31:52.971
Okay. uh. hi. I'm Luigi.

327
00:31:52.972 --> 00:31:54.643
I'm Bowser Jr..

328
00:31:54.644 --> 00:31:58.372
and I'm gonna be
taking my father now.

329
00:32:21.231 --> 00:32:23.297
Whoa.

330
00:32:32.946 --> 00:32:35.342
♪ ♪

331
00:32:35.751 --> 00:32:38.114
Ooh. ooh. ooh.

332
00:33:20.257 --> 00:33:22.060
You've been doing so great.

333
00:33:22.061 --> 00:33:24.601
but thought you might
need a hand.

334
00:33:27.770 --> 00:33:30.540
Ah...

335
00:34:01.364 --> 00:34:03.464
♪ ♪

336
00:34:13.409 --> 00:34:14.409
Dad!

337
00:34:18.249 --> 00:34:19.820
Hold on!

338
00:35:20.212 --> 00:35:22.575
Everyone okay?

339
00:35:24.722 --> 00:35:27.316
Where are we?

340
00:35:31.124 --> 00:35:32.223
Ha!

341
00:35:33.489 --> 00:35:35.292
Sweet freedom!

342
00:35:35.293 --> 00:35:37.162
You got to be kidding me.

343
00:35:37.163 --> 00:35:38.933
Bye. suckers.

344
00:35:38.934 --> 00:35:40.528
Hey. get back here.

345
00:35:40.529 --> 00:35:43.564
No. You can't catch the wind.

346
00:35:48.075 --> 00:35:49.339
I just kind of did.

347
00:35:49.340 --> 00:35:51.275
It was a metaphor!

348
00:35:53.652 --> 00:35:55.785
Ow! Ow! Ow!

349
00:35:55.786 --> 00:35:56.786
Hey.

350
00:35:59.119 --> 00:35:59.855
Ow! Ow!

351
00:36:02.023 --> 00:36:03.617
Never!

352
00:36:07.490 --> 00:36:10.766
You should probably spit him out.

353
00:36:15.036 --> 00:36:15.838
Ooh.

354
00:36:15.839 --> 00:36:18.368
That was intense.

355
00:36:18.369 --> 00:36:21.569
Guys. this is embarrassing.

356
00:36:21.570 --> 00:36:24.913
I'm still a tiny
work in progress.

357
00:36:24.914 --> 00:36:25.881
Sorry. pal.

358
00:36:25.882 --> 00:36:28.345
You expect me to shake
the hand of the turtle

359
00:36:28.346 --> 00:36:30.787
whose son just attacked me?

360
00:36:30.788 --> 00:36:33.646
My son?

361
00:36:35.485 --> 00:36:38.157
I haven't seen him in years.

362
00:36:38.158 --> 00:36:42.194
Mario. I was a terrible father.

363
00:36:42.195 --> 00:36:44.031
He must hate me.

364
00:36:44.032 --> 00:36:45.032
Hate you?

365
00:36:45.033 --> 00:36:48.497
Your son tried to chop
my head off just to free you.

366
00:36:48.498 --> 00:36:50.367
He wants to see you.

367
00:36:50.368 --> 00:36:53.843
He could just use
some guidance.

368
00:36:53.844 --> 00:36:54.712
Really?

369
00:36:54.713 --> 00:36:58.639
You think I might have a shot
at reconnecting with my boy?

370
00:36:58.640 --> 00:36:59.574
Aw. See. Mario?

371
00:36:59.575 --> 00:37:02.885
He's gotten really in touch
with his feelings.

372
00:37:02.886 --> 00:37:04.150
I'm drowning in 'em.

373
00:37:04.151 --> 00:37:05.514
All right.
let's just keep moving.

374
00:37:05.515 --> 00:37:10.023
We got to find a way off
this planet and get to Peach.

375
00:37:10.289 --> 00:37:13.026
♪ ♪

376
00:37:28.175 --> 00:37:30.747
Look! There it is!

377
00:37:45.390 --> 00:37:47.358
♪ ♪

378
00:37:48.723 --> 00:37:51.461
Whoa.

379
00:37:51.462 --> 00:37:55.002
Come on. We're gonna be late.

380
00:37:55.268 --> 00:37:59.776
Whoa. The Gateway Galaxy.

381
00:38:05.113 --> 00:38:08.016
Welcome to Gateway Galaxy.

382
00:38:08.017 --> 00:38:10.854
Your gateway to the galaxies.

383
00:38:14.958 --> 00:38:16.222
Toad. where are you going?

384
00:38:16.223 --> 00:38:19.455
This must be
who we're looking for.

385
00:38:37.739 --> 00:38:39.916
No! No!

386
00:38:43.778 --> 00:38:45.185
Princess?

387
00:38:45.186 --> 00:38:47.549
Are you okay?

388
00:38:52.622 --> 00:38:54.524
Ukiki is lost.

389
00:38:54.525 --> 00:38:58.429
Have you seen Ukiki's friends?

390
00:38:58.430 --> 00:38:59.232
Oh.

391
00:38:59.233 --> 00:39:01.432
We've got a lost little monkey.

392
00:39:01.433 --> 00:39:04.138
I got ya. I got ya.

393
00:39:06.141 --> 00:39:09.737
That monkey just used
his cuteness for crime!

394
00:39:09.738 --> 00:39:10.705
Toad. wait.

395
00:39:10.706 --> 00:39:13.675
All of our Power-Ups
and coins are in there.

396
00:39:13.676 --> 00:39:16.710
And my unfinished novel!

397
00:39:17.482 --> 00:39:20.780
- Pardon me.
- Excuse me. Sorry.

398
00:39:21.783 --> 00:39:22.783
Got him.

399
00:39:30.902 --> 00:39:32.694
We got you now.

400
00:39:38.635 --> 00:39:41.306
Monkey jumped through the wall!

401
00:40:09.633 --> 00:40:11.271
Stay close.

402
00:40:23.878 --> 00:40:26.582
♪ ♪

403
00:40:32.656 --> 00:40:33.557
Hey. you!

404
00:40:35.934 --> 00:40:37.231
Hey!

405
00:40:37.232 --> 00:40:39.463
Give me my backpack!

406
00:40:50.509 --> 00:40:52.950
Dad. I know you're
down there somewhere.

407
00:40:54.711 --> 00:40:56.745
Sire. it is hopeless.

408
00:40:56.746 --> 00:40:59.682
The important thing now
in our time of grief

409
00:40:59.683 --> 00:41:04.126
is to stay strong
for each other.

410
00:41:04.127 --> 00:41:06.557
Will you get ahold of yourself?

411
00:41:06.558 --> 00:41:09.032
We got to keep looking
for Papa.

412
00:41:10.595 --> 00:41:12.926
♪ ♪

413
00:41:14.797 --> 00:41:18.767
So. um. Bowser wants to talk
to you about something.

414
00:41:20.869 --> 00:41:21.803
You know. Mario.

415
00:41:21.804 --> 00:41:25.213
all boys believe their fathers
are larger than life.

416
00:41:25.214 --> 00:41:29.514
I don't want to disappoint
my boy by being so small.

417
00:41:29.515 --> 00:41:31.615
I'm not making you big.

418
00:41:31.616 --> 00:41:35.355
You're used to living
a pint-sized life.

419
00:41:35.356 --> 00:41:37.258
but I was born to be big!

420
00:41:37.259 --> 00:41:39.128
Undo the power
of the Blue Mushroom.

421
00:41:39.129 --> 00:41:43.066
and I shall fight by your side
for all of eternity.

422
00:41:43.067 --> 00:41:44.595
That's a good deal.

423
00:41:44.596 --> 00:41:46.366
Eternity's a long time.

424
00:41:46.367 --> 00:41:48.566
We will be unstoppable.

425
00:41:48.567 --> 00:41:49.831
Hmm.

426
00:41:49.832 --> 00:41:52.405
- No.
- Come on. hit me. Mario.

427
00:41:52.406 --> 00:41:53.175
Hit me!

428
00:41:53.176 --> 00:41:54.737
Yeah. Mario. hit him.
We-we can trust him.

429
00:41:54.738 --> 00:41:57.839
- Hit me!
- Mario. just go ahead and hit him.

430
00:41:57.840 --> 00:41:58.807
- Come on.
- Ha!

431
00:41:58.808 --> 00:42:03.712
Hit me now. you tiny.
pathetic failure of a plumber!

432
00:42:26.374 --> 00:42:29.177
You will not regret this.

433
00:42:31.346 --> 00:42:33.050
Aw.

434
00:42:33.051 --> 00:42:34.645
What are you guys waiting for?

435
00:42:34.646 --> 00:42:36.317
There's a castle up there.

436
00:42:36.318 --> 00:42:38.385
Come on. Follow me.

437
00:42:38.386 --> 00:42:41.157
♪ ♪

438
00:42:42.225 --> 00:42:44.424
Hey!

439
00:42:50.728 --> 00:42:52.564
Sorry.

440
00:42:52.565 --> 00:42:53.466
Whoa!

441
00:42:55.502 --> 00:42:58.206
♪ ♪

442
00:43:00.507 --> 00:43:02.936
Whoa.

443
00:43:22.661 --> 00:43:25.563
♪ ♪

444
00:43:30.504 --> 00:43:32.471
Princess.

445
00:43:34.343 --> 00:43:37.476
♪ ♪

446
00:43:47.191 --> 00:43:52.085
Ukiki.
look at what you brought me.

447
00:43:55.628 --> 00:44:00.367
Princesses are very valuable.

448
00:44:00.798 --> 00:44:03.536
Ukiki thinks your novel stinks!

449
00:44:03.537 --> 00:44:04.537
Ow!

450
00:44:10.148 --> 00:44:10.972
What is it

451
00:44:10.973 --> 00:44:15.009
with you princesses
and getting captured?

452
00:44:15.010 --> 00:44:18.385
You know something about
that missing princess?

453
00:44:19.113 --> 00:44:20.718
Mmm.

454
00:44:20.719 --> 00:44:23.820
Not a thing.

455
00:44:23.821 --> 00:44:26.163
You listen to me.
you slimeball.

456
00:44:26.164 --> 00:44:30.398
You're gonna tell me exactly
where Rosalina is.

457
00:44:30.399 --> 00:44:32.597
Or what?

458
00:45:03.993 --> 00:45:06.027
Oh. Princess.

459
00:45:06.028 --> 00:45:09.096
You're going to regret that.

460
00:45:12.309 --> 00:45:15.211
Oh!

461
00:45:32.120 --> 00:45:34.462
♪ ♪

462
00:45:36.762 --> 00:45:39.995
("Power-Up" plays)

463
00:45:39.996 --> 00:45:42.568
♪ ♪

464
00:45:48.906 --> 00:45:50.742
Hyah!

465
00:45:50.743 --> 00:45:53.249
♪ ♪

466
00:45:55.143 --> 00:45:56.484
Hyah!

467
00:45:56.485 --> 00:45:58.749
Oh!

468
00:46:21.279 --> 00:46:23.709
♪ ♪

469
00:46:25.943 --> 00:46:28.416
Ooh. yes!

470
00:46:53.905 --> 00:46:55.642
Where is she?

471
00:46:55.643 --> 00:46:58.842
Do I look like a snitch?

472
00:46:59.141 --> 00:47:01.076
("Power-Up" plays)

473
00:47:01.077 --> 00:47:02.880
Oh! Yes. I do.

474
00:47:02.881 --> 00:47:04.651
This is your last chance.

475
00:47:04.652 --> 00:47:06.048
Okay. okay. Listen to me.

476
00:47:06.049 --> 00:47:08.820
- Bowser's kid took her.
- Where?

477
00:47:08.821 --> 00:47:11.283
The Space Junk Galaxy.

478
00:47:15.828 --> 00:47:17.433
Toad.

479
00:47:17.434 --> 00:47:20.160
Give me that.

480
00:47:21.405 --> 00:47:25.704
Get me Bowser Jr. now!

481
00:47:27.543 --> 00:47:31.039
Move those little legs. shortcake.

482
00:47:33.384 --> 00:47:34.208
Hi.

483
00:47:34.209 --> 00:47:36.518
We need some help
getting off your planet.

484
00:47:36.519 --> 00:47:38.487
You will have to speak
to the queen.

485
00:47:38.488 --> 00:47:41.391
But the scary-looking guy
stays here.

486
00:47:41.392 --> 00:47:42.722
Hmm.

487
00:47:42.723 --> 00:47:45.021
I got this.

488
00:47:45.022 --> 00:47:47.990
♪ ♪

489
00:47:50.159 --> 00:47:51.401
Hello. Your Highness.

490
00:47:51.402 --> 00:47:54.800
We are trying to get
to the Gateway Galax...

491
00:47:54.801 --> 00:47:59.574
You're the aliens who destroyed
my flower fields.

492
00:47:59.575 --> 00:48:01.169
Imprison them!

493
00:48:01.170 --> 00:48:03.676
Take them to the honey mines!

494
00:48:05.207 --> 00:48:07.911
Not on my watch.

495
00:48:10.487 --> 00:48:13.313
Someone must pay
for their crimes.

496
00:48:13.314 --> 00:48:14.347
Release them!

497
00:48:14.348 --> 00:48:16.723
I shall serve their sentence
in their stead.

498
00:48:16.724 --> 00:48:19.495
I can do the work
of a hundred men

499
00:48:19.496 --> 00:48:21.530
and at least 10.000 bees.

500
00:48:21.531 --> 00:48:26.194
Take me and send them
to the Gateway Galaxy.

501
00:48:32.168 --> 00:48:33.333
Hmm.

502
00:48:33.334 --> 00:48:34.576
We have a deal.

503
00:48:34.577 --> 00:48:37.205
Get them to the Gateway Galaxy.

504
00:48:40.242 --> 00:48:42.583
Are you sure about this?

505
00:48:43.883 --> 00:48:47.280
You're not as horrible
as I thought.

506
00:48:47.755 --> 00:48:49.525
Thank you.

507
00:48:49.526 --> 00:48:50.988
Put that away.

508
00:48:53.090 --> 00:48:55.157
You take care of him. okay?

509
00:48:55.158 --> 00:48:56.598
I always do.

510
00:48:56.599 --> 00:49:01.932
This miserable bug
will give you passage.

511
00:49:07.203 --> 00:49:08.544
Go!

512
00:49:08.545 --> 00:49:11.480
Make your old enemy proud.

513
00:49:19.116 --> 00:49:21.853
♪ ♪

514
00:49:32.129 --> 00:49:35.736
When I'm free. me and my girl
are gonna go dancing

515
00:49:35.737 --> 00:49:37.265
till the sun rises.

516
00:49:37.266 --> 00:49:39.476
You got a honey back home?

517
00:49:40.709 --> 00:49:42.644
She bailed at the altar.

518
00:49:42.645 --> 00:49:44.712
Left me twisted in the wind.

519
00:49:44.713 --> 00:49:46.483
I'm still healing.

520
00:49:46.484 --> 00:49:50.013
remembering who I was
before her.

521
00:49:50.114 --> 00:49:53.181
That is one sensitive soul.

522
00:49:56.989 --> 00:49:58.121
Huh?

523
00:49:58.122 --> 00:49:59.023
Stay strong!

524
00:49:59.024 --> 00:50:01.223
You'll find
the right one someday!

525
00:50:02.863 --> 00:50:06.161
Ooh.

526
00:50:09.463 --> 00:50:11.607
Hi. Dad.

527
00:50:11.608 --> 00:50:12.839
Junior?

528
00:50:12.840 --> 00:50:16.138
Oh. my boy!

529
00:50:17.240 --> 00:50:19.911
You got so big.

530
00:50:20.309 --> 00:50:22.881
This is all yours?

531
00:50:23.147 --> 00:50:26.314
Hey. aren't you supposed
to be at boarding school?

532
00:50:26.315 --> 00:50:27.282
Boarding school?

533
00:50:27.283 --> 00:50:28.756
More like boring school.

534
00:50:28.757 --> 00:50:29.922
I got expelled.

535
00:50:30.825 --> 00:50:33.959
You really grew up
when I wasn't paying attention.

536
00:50:33.960 --> 00:50:35.598
Dad. we're about to become

537
00:50:35.599 --> 00:50:39.635
the two most powerful dudes
in the universe.

538
00:50:39.636 --> 00:50:41.065
Remember when
I was a baby turtle?

539
00:50:41.066 --> 00:50:44.904
You were working so hard
trying to conquer the world.

540
00:50:44.905 --> 00:50:46.576
But once in a while.
you'd have a night off.

541
00:50:46.577 --> 00:50:50.613
and you'd tuck me in and tell
me our favorite bedtime story.

542
00:50:50.614 --> 00:50:54.143
Those were the best nights
of my life.

543
00:50:54.310 --> 00:50:55.882
Tell me the story.

544
00:50:55.883 --> 00:50:57.279
Again?

545
00:51:11.635 --> 00:51:13.427
Back in the days of yore.

546
00:51:13.428 --> 00:51:17.134
there was a powerful villain
with awesome hair.

547
00:51:17.135 --> 00:51:19.708
He loved conquering everything.

548
00:51:22.536 --> 00:51:26.439
You see.
this villain had a son.

549
00:51:27.112 --> 00:51:28.277
The two roamed the universe

550
00:51:28.278 --> 00:51:30.213
desperate for a place
to call home.

551
00:51:30.214 --> 00:51:35.020
but everywhere they went
was just incredibly lame.

552
00:51:35.021 --> 00:51:35.823
Gross!

553
00:51:35.824 --> 00:51:38.991
So they decided
to make their own planet.

554
00:51:38.992 --> 00:51:41.829
Behold Planet Bowser.

555
00:51:41.830 --> 00:51:43.160
a sinister sanctuary

556
00:51:43.161 --> 00:51:45.734
where they could spend
the rest of their days.

557
00:51:45.735 --> 00:51:48.528
They built
an evil roller coaster.

558
00:51:48.529 --> 00:51:49.804
a gorge full of lava.

559
00:51:49.805 --> 00:51:54.303
And they carved a giant mountain into
the shape of their heads.

560
